article.headline: San Diego 66, Alcorn St. 65
article.story: NEW ORLEANS, La. -- Johnny Dee scored 18 points and went 4 for 4 from the free throw line to help San Diego hold on and beat Alcorn State 66-65 Saturday. Darian Norris scored 15 points for the Toreros, going 6 of 8 from the field and 2 of 3 from 3-point range. Chris Manresa recorded 10 points and nine rebounds for San Diego (4-1). Ian Francis and JaMichael Hawkins both scored 12 points and Twann Oakley added 11 points for Alcorn State. Alcorn State (1-4) outshot San Diego from the field, 47.2 percent (25 of 53) to 46.3 percent (25 of 54), and from 3-point range, 43.8 percent (7 of 16) to 35.3 percent (6 of 17), but missed three key free throws in the second half. After being outscored 38-29 in the first half, the Braves outscored the Toreros 36-28 in the second half but fell just short of a comeback win.
